    Note over User,S3: Workflow 1: Notebook Development to Pipeline Execution

    User->>Dashboard: Create notebook workbench<br/>HTTPS/443 OAuth
    Dashboard->>NotebookCtrl: Create Notebook CR
    NotebookCtrl->>Notebook: Create StatefulSet +<br/>Route + OAuth proxy
    User->>Router: Access notebook<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS reencrypt
    Router->>Notebook: Forward to OAuth proxy<br/>8443/TCP
    User->>Notebook: Develop & train model<br/>Submit pipeline via Elyra
    Notebook->>DSP: Submit pipeline<br/>HTTPS/8443 OAuth
    DSP->>Tekton: Create PipelineRun
    Tekton->>S3: Store artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443

    Note over User,S3: Workflow 2: KServe Serverless Model Deployment

    User->>KServeCtrl: Create InferenceService CR
    KServeCtrl->>Knative: Create Knative Service +<br/>VirtualService
    Knative->>S3: Storage Initializer<br/>downloads model artifacts
    OdhModelCtrl->>IstioGW: Create Route in istio-system +<br/>NetworkPolicies + PeerAuth
    User->>IstioGW: POST /v2/models/{name}/infer<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS passthrough
    IstioGW->>ModelPod: Forward via Knative<br/>mTLS STRICT
    ModelPod-->>IstioGW: Prediction response
    IstioGW-->>User: JSON response

    Note over User,S3: Workflow 3: ModelMesh Multi-Model Deployment

    User->>MMCtrl: Create InferenceService<br/>(ModelMesh annotation)
    MMCtrl->>MMPod: Create Deployment with<br/>ModelMesh sidecar + adapter
    MMPod->>S3: Pull model from storage<br/>HTTPS/443
    OdhModelCtrl->>Router: Create Route + ServiceAccount
    User->>Router: gRPC/8033 or REST/8008<br/>HTTPS/443
    Router->>MMPod: Forward to ModelMesh

    Note over User,TrustyAI: Workflow 4: AI Fairness Monitoring

    User->>TrustyAI: Create TrustyAIService CR
    TrustyAI->>MMPod: Patch for payload logging
    MMPod->>TrustyAI: Send inference payloads<br/>HTTP/80
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Compute SPD/DIR metrics
    Note right of TrustyAI: Prometheus scrapes<br/>fairness metrics
